# 3. あの人の教え

Haruka: Phew... We're moving much more in sync now.
ASRUN Members: Yeah, we've totally got this formation down!
Haruka: Then, let's start putting polish on the dance itself.
ASRUN Member A: ...
Haruka: Hm...?
Haruka: Is everything okay? You don't look too good. Are you not feeling well?
ASRUN Member A: Oh, no... It's not that...
Haruka: ...?
ASRUN Members: Huh? What's wrong?
ASRUN Member A: The thing is... I just overheard our manager talking on the phone and...
ASRUN Members: Oh, what did you hear?
ASRUN Member A: You know the show “Go Wild & Crazy!”...?
Haruka: Oh, that daytime show that's run practically forever?
ASRUN Members: Just once, I wanna go on! I mean, there's no one in Japan who hasn't heard of it!
ASRUN Member A: ASRUN was asked to start appearing as regulars, but Mr. Hiiragi turned them down.
Everyone: What...?!
Haruka: (He turned down an offer like that...?!)
ASRUN Members: Wh-Why...?! People all over Japan watch “Go Wild & Crazy!”
ASRUN Members: Right? Appearing as regulars would give us a huge boost in terms of name recognition...
ASRUN Members: It'd be a chance for us to start spreading hope to people all across Japan like the other top idol groups...
Manager: Would you mind stopping by the office after you're finished with practice, Haruka? Mr. Hiiragi would like a word with you.
Haruka: Huh...?
Haruka: Okay, understood.
???: Kiritani.
Haruka: Oh...
Haruka: Hello, Mr. Hiiragi.
Hiiragi: Hello. Sorry, I know this is sudden, but I received an offer asking for you and you alone.
Haruka: Just me?
Hiiragi: That's right. You're being asked to participate in a performance battle, where you and a few other idols will compete to see who can come up with the best dance routine on the spot.
Hiiragi: This is a chance to showcase not just yourself, but the technical prowess of ASRUN as a whole. Keep that in mind.
Haruka: ...! Right!
Hiiragi: I'll send the details over to your manager. That's all from me.
Haruka: E-Excuse me...!
Hiiragi: ...? What's wrong?
Haruka: There's a question I'd like to ask.
Haruka: Is it true that you turned down an offer involving us becoming regulars on “Go Wild & Crazy!”?
Hiiragi: ...
Hiiragi: Honestly... I'll need to remind your manager not to take calls where people can hear him.
Haruka: W-Wait, so...!
Hiiragi: It's all true.
Haruka: Would it be alright if I asked why?
Haruka: We're trying to become idols who can spread hope to people all across Japan. I can't figure out any reason to...
Hiiragi: That very dream is why I turned them down.
Haruka: Huh...?
Hiiragi: Why has ASRUN been able to become as popular as it has?
Hiiragi: Because it's never lost sight of what makes it special.
Haruka: What makes us special...?
Hiiragi: Yes. I believe that idols need to feel unique in some way.
Hiiragi: In other words, ASRUN must offer something that other idols or artists can't hope to emulate. That's what sets your group apart from them.
Hiiragi: Your fans will be drawn to that, and they'll be willing to cheer at the top of their lungs for you.
Haruka: Cheer...
Hiiragi: Yes, in support of your dream. To make it come true together.
Hiiragi: They're absolutely crucial.
Haruka: Oh...
Haruka: (Hearing our fans cheer us on and feel encouraged by what we do has been huge in terms of us getting this far...)
Haruka: (Some have even reached out to their friends and family and invited them to cheer us on together...)
Haruka: (We started out selling CDs by hand at shopping malls, and now look how far we've come.)
Haruka: (Their voices, their support... They kept driving ASRUN forward.)
Hiiragi: Yes, it's important to use high-profile programs to increase your name recognition.
Hiiragi: But establishing a loyal fan base takes absolute priority. Finding those who will cheer at the top of their lungs for you is beyond important.
Haruka: At the top of their lungs...
Hiiragi: What do you think it is that makes ASRUN special, Kiritani?
Haruka: ...
Haruka: (What makes us special... What separates us from everyone else in our fans' minds?)
Haruka: Our performances?
Hiiragi: Correct.
Hiiragi: Your brilliant smiles, your compelling dances, the way your voices ring out towards the back... They inspire hope in everyone watching.
Hiiragi: That's the kind of idol group ASRUN is.
Haruka: ...!
Hiiragi: That being said, I didn't make my decision regarding “Go Wild & Crazy!” lightly. I just felt that now wasn't the right time yet.
Hiiragi: People need to understand what ASRUN is actually about. Until that image is solidified in the public eye...
Hiiragi: I want to place what makes ASRUN special at the forefront, even if it means we do things small for a while.
Hiiragi: Because I believe that's the quickest way for your group to realize its dream.
Haruka: (All I'd been thinking about until now was “spreading hope to lots of people.”)
Haruka: (I never thought about the best way to actually reach that goal.)
Haruka: (But...)
Haruka: (Mr. Hiiragi's looking that far ahead...?)
Haruka: Thank you very much. I really appreciate you telling me all this.
Hiiragi: Not a problem. More importantly, I have high expectations for your next show.
Hiiragi: Go show everyone what makes ASRUN special. That's going to be your ticket to the future.
Haruka: We will!
Haruka: Show everyone what makes us special...
Haruka: Right... He always accepted offers that would place what made ASRUN special at the forefront.
Haruka: That's what we've been missing.
Haruka: But...
Haruka: What is it that makes MORE MORE JUMP! special?
Haruka: We've been doing our best to put on good performances, but we can't really match the groups that have professional choreographers and trainers working with them...
Haruka: As for our talking skills... There's Airi, of course, and Minori also has a natural talent for making others smile and laugh. Still, I'm not sure that's what makes us special.
Haruka: But...
Haruka: (I know there's something there. I just can't quite put it into words.)
Haruka: This is really frustrating... How do I find the right words for what I'm feeling?
Haruka: I want to ask the others about this, but it's already pretty late. I should probably wait until tomorrow...
Haruka: Oh...
Haruka: Yeah. I'll try popping over for a little bit to ask them.
